Colin Ritman? That's crazy.
I've played all of his games.

01:36:45.240 --> 01:36:48.240
State of him, he's made enough
this year to buy a Lamborghini

01:36:48.320 --> 01:36:50.240
and he still smokes roll-ups.

01:36:55.640 --> 01:36:58.400
-We've met before.
-No.

01:37:01.320 --> 01:37:02.840
This is what I'm working on.

01:37:04.240 --> 01:37:07.640
-Nohzdyve.
-Yeah. That's right.

01:37:13.960 --> 01:37:15.120
[Colin] Oh, bollocks.

01:37:15.200 --> 01:37:16.880
-What's that?
-Buffer error.

01:37:18.600 --> 01:37:21.760
Those eyeball sprites overshot
the video memory.

01:37:23.240 --> 01:37:24.440
How did you know that?

01:37:25.600 --> 01:37:28.280
-Just did.
-Bloody hell, he's good, right?

01:37:28.760 --> 01:37:33.200
Anyway, let's get down to business.
Stefan's got something to demo for us.

01:37:35.080 --> 01:37:37.720
[Stefan] You choose with the joystick.
See. You've got ten seconds.

01:37:38.280 --> 01:37:40.120
Don't worship him,
he's the Thief of Destiny.

01:37:40.760 --> 01:37:43.680
-You've read<i> Bandersnatch?</i>
-Jerome F. Davies. Visionary.

01:37:43.800 --> 01:37:46.280
Was he that bloke who went cuckoo
and cut his wife's head off?

01:37:46.800 --> 01:37:48.520
That is what people tend to focus on, yes.

01:37:48.600 --> 01:37:51.280
Which ending did you get?
When you read it.

01:37:51.360 --> 01:37:52.720
-All of them.
-Excuse me.

01:37:57.080 --> 01:37:59.920
-What's happened?
-I haven't programmed that path yet.

01:38:00.000 --> 01:38:02.280
Right. So, a lot of paths then?

01:38:02.720 --> 01:38:05.000
Well, yes,
if it's going to be like the book.

01:38:05.080 --> 01:38:06.680
A lot of divergent realities in that book.

01:38:07.080 --> 01:38:10.560
It was ahead of its time.
In as much as time exists.

01:38:11.960 --> 01:38:16.080
OK. So here's my proposal.
Come and write it here.

01:38:17.160 --> 01:38:18.000
Here?

